        "created_at": "2025-12-05T13:22:03.881Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Have you ever considered eliminating the wait time for those of us who are chatting as if we were talking? For when you‚Äôre connected, not a message they‚Äôll answer when they can but hi yes lets chat, without the whole messages sent‚Ä¶wait wait‚Ä¶messages delivered‚Ä¶wait wait‚Ä¶messages read. I get it but shouldn‚Äôt chatting have an immediate we‚Äôre both here in the moment aspect to it? I‚Äôm also addressing the whole if you reply immediately all those checks go away anyway but if you want to view them as separate replies you can‚Äôt it just all gets lumped together, no separation between he said she said unless you choose edit, then only the first sent check shows but the other person is the only one that triggers the delivered check or the read solid color. If we‚Äôre talking/texting in real time why is it more like email than a direct one to one chat? Without having to use the phone either or even the audio only. It is still ‚Äútexting‚Äù isn‚Äôt it? Maybe it‚Äôs just me.</p>",
