        "created_at": "2025-12-05T14:58:06.321Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That would be synchronous messaging, which is how instant messaging worked 30+ years ago. The world moved to asynchronous messaging as it unchained from desktops and laptops and went always-on mobile with Blackberries etc.</p>\n<p>If Signal were synchronous, you‚Äôd never know if you had new messages until you opened the app, and that‚Äôs not compatible with the way people use smartphones and computers in 2025.</p>\n<p>Edit: comparison: <a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/system-design/synchronous-vs-asynchronous-communication-system-design/?utm_source=perplexity\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Synchronous vs. Asynchronous Communication - System Design - GeeksforGeeks</a></p>\n<p>If you want to talk in real time, that‚Äôs what audio and video calling are for.</p>",
